<h5 id="brackets">brackets</h5>
<ol>
  <li>curly brackets: {} which means the order doesn‚Äôt matter.</li>
  <li>square brackets: [] the order matters.</li>
  <li>tilde $ \tilde $ means: denote an equivalence between two objects.x $ \tilde $y</li>
  <li>raised asterisk $*$: used to denote adjoint.</li>
  <li>hat over letter: used to denote an estimated value, as opposed to its
theoretical counterpart, for example, in the context of errors and residuals,
the ‚Äúhat‚Äù over the letter $\epsilon$ indicates an observable estimate (the
residuals) of an unobservable quantity called $\epsilon$(the statistical
errors).</li>
</ol>

